If `SimpleExoPlayer` is deprecated, you might need to migrate to the new recommended classes or interfaces provided by ExoPlayer. Always refer to the latest documentation to ensure you are using the most up-to-date and supported features.

Here's a simple migration example:

```java
// Before
SimpleExoPlayer player = new SimpleExoPlayer.Builder(context).build();

// After (using ExoPlayer)
ExoPlayer player = new ExoPlayer.Builder(context).build();
```

Remember to check the official ExoPlayer documentation or release notes for any specific instructions regarding deprecated classes and their replacements.

[ASSISTANT] Custom track selection in ExoPlayer involves implementing a custom `TrackSelector` to control how tracks (video, audio, text) are selected for playback. This is particularly useful when you want to prioritize specific qualities, formats, or adapt the track selection based on custom criteria. Below, I'll provide a basic example of implementing a custom `TrackSelector` for video tracks.

```java
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.DefaultLoadControl;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.DefaultRenderersFactory;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.ExoPlayer;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.SimpleExoPlayer;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.trackselection.DefaultTrackSelector;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.trackselection.TrackSelection;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.trackselection.TrackSelector;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.upstream.DefaultBandwidthMeter;
import com.google.android.exoplayer2.upstream.DefaultDataSourceFactory;

public class CustomTrackSelectionExample {

    private ExoPlayer exoPlayer;

    // Initialize ExoPlayer with a custom TrackSelector
    private void initializePlayer() {
        DefaultRenderersFactory renderersFactory = new DefaultRenderersFactory(context);
        DefaultTrackSelector trackSelector = new CustomTrackSelector(context);
        DefaultLoadControl loadControl = new DefaultLoadControl();

        exoPlayer = new SimpleExoPlayer.Builder(context, renderersFactory)
                .setTrackSelector(trackSelector)
                .setLoadControl(loadControl)
                .build();
    }

    // Custom TrackSelector implementation
    private static class CustomTrackSelector extends DefaultTrackSelector {

        public CustomTrackSelector(Context context) {
            super(context);
        }

        @Override
        protected TrackSelection[] selectTracks(RendererCapabilities[] rendererCapabilities,
                                               TrackGroupArray[] rendererTrackGroupArrays,
                                               int[][][] rendererFormatSupports) {
            // Implement your custom track selection logic here
            // For example, prioritize higher resolution video tracks
            // You can access track information through rendererCapabilities and rendererTrackGroupArrays

            // Return the selected track selections
            return super.selectTracks(rendererCapabilities, rendererTrackGroupArrays, rendererFormatSupports);
        }
    }
}
```

In the example above, `CustomTrackSelector` extends `DefaultTrackSelector`, and the `selectTracks` method is overridden to provide custom track selection logic. You can inspect `rendererCapabilities` and `rendererTrackGroupArrays` to access information about available tracks and their properties.

This is a basic example, and the actual implementation will depend on your specific requirements. You might consider factors like bandwidth, device capabilities, or user preferences when implementing a custom track selector. Always refer to the latest ExoPlayer documentation for the most up-to-date information and best practices.

